{
  "texts": [
    "Note that the boundary twistors and dual twistors scale in the appropriate way; z α ∼ tz α and w α ∼ t -1 w α.",
    "One would then recover different signatures as different real slices on the corresponding spaces.",
    "It is straightforward to include the fermionic variables in a supertwistor spaceZ M = Z m W m ∈ CP 1|2 × CP 1|2, where Z m = ξ α ψ A, W m = η α χ A.The worldsheet action and stress tensor have simple descriptions in these variables,S = d 2 z W m DZ m +... = 1 2 d 2 z Z M DZ M +... +, T = 1 2 Z M ∂Z M + T σ + T ρ + T C,where the ellipses denote contributions from the antiholomorphic, ghost and T 4 sectors.",
    "We raise (lower) supertwistor indices using Ω M N (Ω M N), where Ω M N is the natural symplectic form given by the (anti-)commutation relationsZ M, Z N ± = Ω M N. 13The local symmetry Q(z) we encountered in section 2.1 can also be interpreted naturally in these coordinates as the pull-back of a holomorphic measure along a CP 1|2 in the boundary twistor space.",
    "Q has projective weight zero and so we can introduce a non-local operator given by integrating Q over a CP 1|2 in the target superspace."
  ]
}